\par 
\par "Eh well! How then?" demanded madame, tying another knot, as if there
\par were another enemy strangled.
\par 
\par "Well!" said Defarge, with a half complaining and half apologetic shrug.
\par "We shall not see the triumph."
\par 
\par "We shall have helped it," returned madame, with her extended hand in
\par strong action. "Nothing that we do, is done in vain. I believe, with all
